        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test: make install-safe-path symlink tests compatible with Windows",
        "body": "Replaces the hardcoded Windows skips in the install-safe-path test suite with a dynamic `canCreateDirectorySymlinks` capability check. If directory symlinking is supported by the OS environment, the tests execute.\n\nAdditionally, uses directory junctions (via the `junction` link type) on Windows when creating parent directories to ensure compatibility without Administrator privileges.\n\n### Verified Windows Proof\n\nThe following test execution log shows the test run on Windows. All directory junction/symlink tests executed and passed successfully (24 passed):\n\n```\n RUN  v4.1.7 C:/Users/ANIRUDDHA/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/openclaw\n\n ✓  infra  ../../src/infra/install-safe-path.test.ts (24 tests) 485ms\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  24 passed (24)\n```\n",
